Senate Resolution 281
By: Senators Tillery of the 19th, Strickland of the 42nd, Hatchett of the 50th, Hodges of the
3rd and Echols of the 49th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Talmadge James on the occasion of her retirement; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Talmadge James has long been recognized by the citizens and leaders of this
4 state for the vital role she has played in state and local government and for her deep personal
5 commitment to the State of Georgia; and
6 WHEREAS, for the past 25 years, she has diligently and conscientiously devoted countless
7 hours of her time, talents, and energy toward the betterment of the daily operations of the
8 Georgia General Assembly, as evidenced by her exemplary service in the Georgia House of
9 Representatives; and
10 WHEREAS, Talmadge James began her career with the House of Representatives on April
11 1, 1999, after previously serving as a session assistant in 1998; and
12 WHEREAS, she faithfully assisted both Senate and House members during her service in the
13 Governor's Floor Leader's Office, and she currently serves in the House Majority Leader's
14 Office; and
